HEADWORD: Sob
<hw>Sob</hw> <pr>(s⟦ocr⟧b)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Sop</er>.]</ety> <def>To soak.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sob</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sob
<hw>Sob</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Sobbed</conjf> <pr>(s⟦ocr⟧bd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Sobbing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>sobben</ets>; akin to
AS. <ets>se⟦oacute⟧fian</ets>, <ets>si⟦oacute⟧fian</ets>, to complain,
bewail, <ets>se⟦oacute⟧fung</ets>, <ets>si⟦oacute⟧fung</ets>, sobbing,
lamentation; cf. OHG. <ets>s⟦umac⟧ft⟦omac⟧n</ets>,
<ets>s⟦umac⟧ftj⟦omac⟧n</ets>, to sigh, MHG. <ets>siuften</ets>,
<ets>siufzen</ets>, G. <ets>seufzen</ets>, MHG. <ets>s⟦umac⟧ft</ets> a
sigh, properly, a drawing in of breath, from <ets>s⟦umac⟧fen</ets> to
drink, OHG. <ets>s⟦umac⟧fan</ets>. Cf. <er>Sup</er>.]</ety> <def>To sigh
with a sudden heaving of the breast, or with a kind of convulsive
motion; to sigh with tears, and with a convulsive drawing in of the
breath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sobbing</qex> is the same thing [as sighing], stronger.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She sighed, she <qex>sobbed</qex>, and, furious with despair.⟦br⟧
She rent her garments, and she tore her hair.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sob</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sob
<hw>Sob</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of sobbing; a
convulsive sigh, or inspiration of the breath, as in sorrow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Break, heart, or choke with <qex>sobs</qex> my hated breath.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any sorrowful cry or sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The tremulous <qex>sob</qex> of the complaining owl.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sobbing</ent>⟦br⟧
